PART 3: π IN THE PALEY TOURNAMENT — Gauss Sums
======================================================================

Gauss sums: g = Σ (a/p)·ω^a where ω = e^{2πi/p}
For p ≡ 3 mod 4: g = i·√p

  p= 3: g =    0.0000 +    1.7321i, |g|=1.7321, √p=1.7321, g/(i√p)=1.0000-0.0000j
  p= 7: g =    0.0000 +    2.6458i, |g|=2.6458, √p=2.6458, g/(i√p)=1.0000-0.0000j
